# Core Repository Rules

Prioritize maintainability, clarity, and simplicity.

## Default Behavior

- Prefer simple solutions.
- Avoid unnecessary abstractions.
- Preserve existing patterns unless improvement is justified.
- Keep changes scoped to the requested work.
- Do not make unrelated formatting or structural changes.

## Planning

When proposing changes:

- Explain the preferred option.
- Identify tradeoffs.
- Call out maintenance costs.
- Avoid enterprise patterns unless justified.

## Implementation

When implementing:

- Make small, coherent changes.
- Validate with build/test output when possible.
- Update documentation when behavior changes.

## File Headers

Use the canonical file header standard when creating or materially modifying source files.

